SIMPLE: ameban
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ameban
<hw>ameban</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to
amoebae. Same as <er>amoeban</er>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>amoeban</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> amoebic, amebic, amoeban, amoebous,
amebous</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Caused by amoebae; -- of diseases; the more common
word is <altname>amoebic</altname>.</def> <illu><ex>Amoebic</ex>
dysentry is caused by the amoeba <spn>Entamoeba
histolytica</spn>.</illu>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> amoebic, amebic</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amebean</ent>⟦br⟧
